<p>When designing the core ability system for my game, my main inspiration was Fate/kaleid liner Prisma Illya. In this anime, the main character has the ability to transform themselves into different servants with those servants abilities. I belived that this would be a creative game mechanic so I thought of some ways to implement them. For this, I decided to go down the chess root, where the player is a pawn and can promote themselves to any piece they want.</p>



<p>Then, I wanted to find an interesting balance on why the player might want to play a certain piece. To do this I gave each piece their own passive abilities to differentiate themselves. However, for the pawn, they have generic abilities you would expect,  but then I gave the pawn the unique ability to be able to equip active abilities from other classes, making the pawn the most versatile.</p>



